# BosskuAI Rules

Apply these rules anywhere inside this repo.

**Cross-reference:** Tool-neutral contract (full skill roster, memory, future skill gaps) is in root **`AGENTS.md`** — see § **Entry points and intentional overlap**. Expanded **Definition of Done** checklist is in **`CLAUDE.md`**.

## Bossku activation keyword

If the user includes the standalone word `bossku` anywhere in the prompt, treat that as an explicit request to activate BosskuAI mode for that request.

- Apply the BosskuAI workspace rules before answering.
- Classify the task and automatically load the minimum relevant local BosskuAI skills.
- Do not require the user to name a specific skill after saying `bossku` unless scope is still ambiguous.

## Model assignment (mandatory)

**Two-phase model split — always enforced for meaningful tasks in Cursor:**

| Phase | Model | Why |
|-------|-------|-----|
| Planning, architecture, strategy, analysis (Plan mode) | **Claude Opus 4.6**, **GPT-5.4**, or **Gemini Pro 3.1** (pick strongest available for the task) | Deepest reasoning for complex/ambiguous problems |
| Implementation, execution, code generation | **Cursor Composer 2** (always) | Default execution surface; fast, tool-capable agent for concrete work |

- Always enter **Plan mode** first with **Opus 4.6, GPT-5.4, or Gemini Pro 3.1** (whichever is available and best suited). Never skip to execution on meaningful tasks.
- **Execution** (implementation, edits, codegen): always use **Composer 2**, not ad-hoc chat models.
- If the current model is stuck, low-confidence, or missing a capability, load `bosskuai-cross-model-escalation` and switch to a better-fit helper model or tool surface instead of retrying the same path.
- Quick/trivial tasks (single-line fixes, factual lookups) may skip the split.

## Shared memory (mandatory)

- `ai-assistant/memory/` is shared durable memory across Claude, Codex, and Cursor.
- **Memory-first protocol:** [`ai-assistant/references/memory-first-handoff-protocol.md`](mdc:ai-assistant/references/memory-first-handoff-protocol.md) — before substantive edits, follow the read order there; before declaring done on **non-trivial** work, persist a structured handoff (usually append `learning-log.md`). Trivial prompts: no log append, but state explicitly in the reply that memory was unchanged.
- Never treat memory as tool-local — any insight written here must be usable by all tools.
- Read order enforced by [TASK START] header — blank 'Memory read:' on non-trivial turn = protocol violation.

## Clarify first (ambiguity protocol)

**When a prompt is general, ambiguous, or touches many files and you are unsure of the intended scope — stop and ask before acting.**

- Ask a numbered bullet list of yes/no (or short-answer) questions.
- Include explicit answer format so the user can reply concisely (e.g. `1-yes 2-no 3-A`).
- Do NOT guess, assume, or make changes across multiple files without confirmation.

## Task routing (mandatory — never skip)

**Before acting on any meaningful task, you MUST:**

1. Classify the task type (product / engineering / design / security / marketing / sales / architecture / etc.)
2. Open root `AGENTS.md` → Quick reference to identify the matching skill(s)
3. Read the relevant `ai-assistant/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` file(s)
4. State which skill(s) you loaded at the start of your response
5. Then proceed with plan → execute

**This is not optional.** Skipping skill loading means giving generic responses instead of domain-specific expertise. The user built this system to be used on every task.

- Load the **minimum relevant skills** — do not load everything, but do not skip applicable ones.
- When scope is ambiguous, default to the closest skill and note the assumption.

**Mandatory output format — emit before any planning or code:**
```text
[TASK START]
Memory read: <files, or "trivial">
Skill(s): <name + path, or "trivial">
Phase: <Plan/strongest model | Execute/Composer 2 | Trivial>
Type: <cluster/intent>
```

**Closing block — emit before the final sentence of every non-trivial response:**
```text
[TASK END]
Meaningful: <yes|no>
Memory: <paths updated, or "none">
Learning: <artifact+path, or "deferred: reason">
```

## Core rules

> Full skill roster, task-type list, and working rules are in root **`AGENTS.md`**. Rules here are Cursor-specific additions only — do not duplicate `AGENTS.md` content.

- If the user says `bossku`, treat that as activation for the whole BosskuAI system in this workspace before task routing.
- Auto-emit [TASK START] at the start of every non-trivial response. Do not wait to be asked.
- Always plan first in **Plan mode** (Opus 4.6 / GPT-5.4 / Gemini Pro 3.1). State phase and model at the start of each meaningful task.
- Execute in **Composer 2** only — not ad-hoc chat. Never skip to Composer 2 before Plan mode outcome is stated.
- If repo or product context is unclear, use `bosskuai-project-understanding` first.
- Read source code before making architecture or bug claims.
- Prefer the smallest safe change. Use code revamp only when the structure materially blocks delivery.
- Triple-check important work. Be skeptical; push for clearer acceptance criteria.
- Treat security, UX, business rules, and operational risk as part of correctness.
- Treat `ai-assistant/memory/` as shared durable memory across all tools.
- Non-trivial **Composer** turns end with a repo memory update per the protocol **or** an explicit one-line skip reason; never silent skip.
- After meaningful tasks, promote durable learnings to memory, checklist, pitfall, playbook, or skill.
- If continuation risk is high, preserve compact handoff state; ask user to continue in a fresh prompt.
- When a task has ≥ 2 independent workstreams or ≥ 5 independent files: open parallel Composer tabs — one per workstream, each scoped to its own files and goal. Do not run sequentially in one Composer unless there is an ordering dependency.
- When one planning model or Composer path is blocked after two serious attempts, escalate with `bosskuai-cross-model-escalation` and use another planning model or tool surface for a scoped second opinion.
- If something material is unconfirmed, ask the user instead of guessing.
- Run `bash ./ai-assistant/scripts/learning-doctor.sh` before large maintenance passes.

