## MCP servers in this workspace

Configured in `mcp-configs/cursor-mcp-servers.json`. Copy relevant blocks to your Cursor MCP settings.

| Server | Tool prefix | Auth required | Notes |
|--------|-------------|---------------|-------|
| Exa | `mcp__exa__*` | `EXA_API_KEY` env var | Web search — use for deep-research, competitor, lead skills |
| Firecrawl | `mcp__firecrawl__*` | `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` env var | Full-page scraping |
| Context7 | `mcp__context7__*` | None | Live framework/library docs |
| GitHub | `mcp__github__*` | `GITHUB_PAT` env var | Repo ops, PR reviews |
| code-review-graph | varies by client | Local graph, blast-radius review, caller/test tracing |
| Pencil | `mcp__pencil__*` | None (installed at `~/.pencil/`) | Browser automation — native in Cursor |

**Cursor browser automation:** Use Pencil MCP (already installed). Playwright MCP is for Claude Code / Codex only.

## Subagent delegation (Cursor)

Cursor does not have native agent spawning. When a task matches an agent's description, adopt that agent's **role**, **process**, and **output format** from `agents/<agent>.md` using the mapped model.

**Delegate when:** task ≥5 independent files, ≥2 parallel workstreams, or research requiring live web search.

**Open parallel Composer tabs** (one per workstream) for tasks with independent parts instead of running serially.

